\section*{Writing Own class}
\label{writing-own-class}

There are two types of file that contain user-defined style information - classes (\emph{.cls) and packages (}.sty).
A package can be included with any kind of class (article, book) and it will work sensibly. It usually includes things like author information.
A class is much harder to work with other classes - a book class will work badly if it tries to coexist with a newsletter class.

We want a business-report class, that we shall use to define how all the memos and reports we send out to the business shall look. It will try and mimic a Word document as corporate style usually gets defined like that.

